    "Figure 7 shows the projected growth of Internet of Things (IoT) connected devices worldwide from 2020 to 2030.",
    "With the rapid global growth of IoT technology, it is now possible to connect real-world objects to the Internet, enabling applications in healthcare, agriculture, and smart cities (Chataut and Phoummalayvane 2023).",
    "IoT-connected devices are expected to grow exponentially in number, resulting in digitalization and automation of daily lives and industries (Tasgaonkar et al. 2023).",
    "Figure 7 shows that Greater China will have approximately 8.6 billion IoT-connected devices by 2030, the highest number in the world.",
    "IoT device numbers are also expected to be highest in Europe and North America (www.statista.com/statistics)."
